Text: When a claim is received, it is first checked whether the claimant is insured by the organization.
Constraints extracted: [PRECEDENCE(A=receive it, B=the claimant is insured by the organization ), PRECEDENCE(A=the claimant is insured by the organization , B=check it)]

Text: If not, the claimant is informed that the claim must be rejected.
Otherwise, the severity of the claim is evaluated.
Based on the outcome (simple or complex claims), relevant forms are sent to the claimant.
Once the forms are returned, they are checked for completeness.
If the forms provide all relevant details, the claim is registered in the Claims Management system, which ends the Claims Notification process.
Constraints extracted: [PRECEDENCE(A=the forms provide all relevant details , B=register claim)]

Text: Otherwise, the claimant is informed to update the forms.
Upon reception of the updated forms, they are checked again.
